properties.description: Process preceding the triggering of a purchase order. Includes supplier creation.

properties.name: Specify & quantify demand
properties.documentation: Please give details about quantity and product description of the demand. An explanatory statement explaining the demand is also required.

properties.name: Use goods from stock
properties.documentation: The stock for office supplies is located in the main building, floor 4, room 4711.

properties.name: Create purchase requisition
properties.documentation: The purchase requisition needs to be created in transaction TA4711 in the ERP system. Every department has the right to do this.

properties.name: Check purchase requisition
properties.documentation: The check is done via the workflow inbox of the ERP system.

properties.name: Create order template from purchase requisition
properties.documentation: In the ERP system an order template is created from a purchase requisition. With the template the order can be triggered.

properties.name:
Create
supplier in ERP
properties.documentation: Go to transaction SB4711, click on the button "New supplier" and enter the details according to the input fields.

properties.name: Approve & trigger order
properties.documentation: Approval by the department head. The purchase order is then triggered automatically. This is done via the workflow inbox of the ERP system.
